For each physiological parameter, a set of 23 statistics were computed in order to aggregate the physiological data during sleep. The aggregated statistics were: min, max, mean, std, skewness, kurtosis, hyperskewness, hypertailedness, pct_1 (1st percentile), pct_5, pct_10, pct_20, pct_25, pct_30, pct_40, pct_50, pct_60, pct_70, pct_75, pct_80, pct_90, pct_95, pct_99. Thus, yielding a total of 34 physiological parameter \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
